<li>H-NS also inﬂuences the major DNA transactions , such as replication , transposition and recombination [ 5 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16933988" target="_blank">16933988</a>]<br></li>
<li>Both global positive regulators , such as the nucleoid proteins Fis and H-NS or the cyclic AMP ( cAMP ) - catabo-lite activator protein ( CAP ) complex ( 21 -- 23 ) , and negative regulators , such as RﬂM , the Spi1 regulator RtsB , or SlyA , bind within and act upon the ﬂhDC promoter ( 24 , 25 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=24488311" target="_blank">24488311</a>]<br></li>
<li>The proV promoter and the hemX gene were used as positive and negative control regions , respectively , as H-NS binds to the proV promoter and does not bind to the hemX gene [ 71 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27564394" target="_blank">27564394</a>]<br></li>
<li>The Escherichia coli SOS gene sbmC is regulated by H-NS and RpoS during the SOS induction and stationary growth-phase .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21102598" target="_blank">21102598</a>]<br></li>
<li>Positive regulation is mediated by cyclic AMP ( cAMP ) and cAMP receptor protein ( CRP ) complex and the nucleoid protein H-NS ( 1 , 23 , 50 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11790733" target="_blank">11790733</a>]<br></li>
<li>For example , cyclic AMP-CRP [ 43-46 ] , H-NS [ 46,47 ] , QseBC [ 48 ] , CsrA [ 49 ] , and the heat-shock-induced chaperones , DnaK , DnaJ , and GrpE [ 50 ] , function as positive regulators , while negative regulation is mediated by OmpR [ 51 ] , RcsCDB [ 52 ] , LrhA [ 53 ] , and ClpXP [ 54 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19706157" target="_blank">19706157</a>]<br></li>
<li>The ﬂhDC operon is regulated in response to environmental stimuli such as cyclic AMP levels and temperature ( 23 , 53 ) , heat-shock ( 50 ) , osmolarity and membrane biosynthesis ( 22 , 38 , 50 , 51 ) , and the H-NS protein ( 4 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9079927" target="_blank">9079927</a>]<br></li>
<li>This repression is antagonized by SlyA , which competes for binding at the H-NS promoter and allows cyclic AMP receptor protein ( CRP ) and fumarate and nitrate reduction regulator ( FNR ) to activate HlyE expression [ 54,55 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19746165" target="_blank">19746165</a>]<br></li>
<li>This promoter is controlled by a number of global regulators , such as cyclic AMP receptor protein ( 74 , 83 ) , heat-shock proteins DnaK , DnaJ , and GrpE ( 72 ) , and H-NS ( 11 , 82 ) , as well as by several environmental signals , such as temperature , high concentrations of inorganic salts , carbohydrates , or alcohols , growth-phase , DNA supercoiling , phosphatidylethanolamine and phosphatidylglycerol synthesis , and cell cycle control ( 21 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20028809" target="_blank">20028809</a>]<br></li>
<li>Furthermore , other DNA-bending modulators such as IHF and Fis counteract H-NS repression and support virulence gene activation by the virulence cluster/PAI-speci ﬁc activator proteins .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=26441883" target="_blank">26441883</a>]<br></li>
<li>Transcription of hilA is subject to direct or indirect negative control by multiple nucleoid binding proteins , including Hha , H-NS , HU , and Fis ( 10 , 23 ) , and other proteins , including HilE , Pag , and Ams ( 5 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15126488" target="_blank">15126488</a>]<br></li>
<li>Indeed , under inducing conditions , HilD and HilC , and probably RtsA , counteract the strong HilA and RtsA depression triggered by H-NS ( 292 , 293 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23554419" target="_blank">23554419</a>]<br></li>
<li>We propose that a dual signal , pH/CAMP/Mg2 and ppGpp , modulates regulatory activity of the PhoP/PhoQ system and SlyA , respectively , and subsequently stimulates target genes by antagonizing H-NS function .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19091955" target="_blank">19091955</a>]<br></li>
<li>For example , DNA bending and supercoiling may regulate virulence genes as suggested by findings that the small nucleoid binding proteins IHF and H-NS reduce expression of spvR and spvABCD respectively ( O'Byrne and Dorman , 1994 ; Marshall et al. , 1999 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10844688" target="_blank">10844688</a>]<br></li>
<li>The global regulators H-NS and LeuO regulate the assT-dsbL-dsbI cluster expression negatively and positively , respectively , and this regulation depends on speciﬁc growth conditions ( 77 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=25566242" target="_blank">25566242</a>]<br></li>
