<li>We consistently observe that mutations in Hha or point mutations in the dimerization domain of H-NS result in substantial up-regulation of hilA transcription but have little effect on H-NS occupancy at the same region in vivo when measured by ChIP .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23515315" target="_blank">23515315</a>]<br></li>
