<li>The flhDC master operon is influenced by a number of global regulatory signals , including catabolite repression ( c-AMP , CAP ) , temperature , cell-cycle , osmolarity ( OmpR ) , DNA structure ( H-NS ) , stationary phase ( RpoS ) , heat shock ( DnaJ , DnaK , GrpE ) and membrane biosynthesis ( Silverman and Simon , 1974Komeda et al. , 1975 ; Shi et al. , 1992 , 1993a , b ; Amsler et al. , 1993 ; Bertin et al. , 1994 ; Kitamura et al. , 1994 ; Miziyama et al. , 1995 ; Mizushima et al. , 1995 , 1997 ; Shin and Park , 1995 ; PruÈû and Matsumura , 1996 , 1997 ; PruÈû et al. , 1997 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10972838" target="_blank">10972838</a>]<br></li>
<li>H-NS is a nucleoid-associated protein that globally silences genes acquired via horizontal gene transfer ( Lucchini et al. , 2006 ; Navarre et al. , 2006 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21570144" target="_blank">21570144</a>]<br></li>
<li>LeuO is a LysR-type quiescent regulator that is under negative control by H-NS ( Klauck et al. , 1997 ; Chen et al. , B 2005 ; Navarre et al. , 2006 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17908208" target="_blank">17908208</a>]<br></li>
