<li>RcsB-BglJ activates the Escherichia coli leuO gene , encoding an H-NS antagonist and pleiotropic regulator of virulence determinants .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=24659766" target="_blank">24659766</a>]<br></li>
<li>Stratmann T , Pul U , Wurm R , Wagner R , Schnetz K. RcsB-BglJ activates the Escherichia coli leuO gene , encoding an H-NS antagonist and pleiotropic regulator of virulence determinants .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=25566242" target="_blank">25566242</a>]<br></li></div>
<li>Here , LeuO controls a large regulon of genes , including virulence genes , many of which are silenced by H-NS ( Dillon et al. , 2012 ; Cordero-Alba and Ramos-Morales , 2014 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=28631437" target="_blank">28631437</a>]<br></li>
<li>Examples of these methods have been identiﬁed for counter-silencing H-NS at horizontally acquired virulence genes in Salmonella , and their signiﬁcance is discussed below .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=29034217" target="_blank">29034217</a>]<br></li>
<li>In addition , Crp , IHF , Lrp , and H-NS ( 5 , 23 , 29 , 30 , 44 , 49 , 55 , 57 ) have been identiﬁed as modulating factors in the control of various sS-dependent genes ( 39 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8626324" target="_blank">8626324</a>]<br></li>
<li>( A ) Horizontally acquired genes in Salmonella are silenced by H-NS , and cis-regulatory elements can undergo mutations to acquire binding sites that bring these genes under the control of a core virulence regulator such as PhoP .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=29034217" target="_blank">29034217</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=29034217" target="_blank">29034217</a>]<br></li>
<li>Interestingly , members of other transcriptional regulators families such as VirF ( AraC/XilS ) , RovA ( SlyA/Hor ) , and Ler ( H-NS/StpA ) have been described as antagonists of H-NS mainly on genes involved in virulence ( 72 -- 74 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=25566242" target="_blank">25566242</a>]<br></li>
<li>These findings are likely generalizable to pathogens such as E. coli , Yersinia , Shigella , and Vibrio cholerae , all of which maintain a pool of `` expensive '' AT-rich virulence genes that are repressed by H-NS .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=25375226" target="_blank">25375226</a>]<br></li>
<li>Full induction of spv expression has been shown to depend on RpoS , SpvR , H-NS , IHF and a global regulatory component termed leucine response protein ( LRP ) ( 81 , 82 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11370771" target="_blank">11370771</a>]<br></li>
<li>Numerous transcription factors are involved , including OmpR , MlrA , and CpxR and the nonspeciﬁc DNA-binding proteins H-NS and IHF , in addition to the feed-forward loop involving rpoS and the factors that regulate RpoS activity , including IraP and Crl .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=25824832" target="_blank">25824832</a>]<br></li>
<li>These include the Csp family ( CspA , B , E , G and I ) of RNA-binding proteins with RNA chaperone-activity ( Gualerzi , Giuliodori , & Pon , 2003 ) , YmdB , which regulates RNase III activity , and gyrase and H-NS , which negatively supercoil DNA , allowing transcriptional repression ( Kim , Manasherob , & Cohen , 2008 ; Storz & Hengge , 2011 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23651595" target="_blank">23651595</a>]<br></li>
<li>This promoter is controlled by a number of global regulators , such as cyclic AMP receptor protein ( 74 , 83 ) , heat shock proteins DnaK , DnaJ , and GrpE ( 72 ) , and H-NS ( 11 , 82 ) , as well as by several environmental signals , such as temperature , high concentrations of inorganic salts , carbohydrates , or alcohols , growth phase , DNA supercoiling , phosphatidylethanolamine and phosphatidylglycerol-synthesis , and cell-cycle control ( 21 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20028809" target="_blank">20028809</a>]<br></li>
<li>Flagellar regulation is highly complex and is orchestrated at the levels of transcription , translation , ﬂagellum assembly , and stability , involving a large number of positive and negative regulators , including SirA/BarA ( 38 ) , RtsB ( 39 ) , SlyA and LrhA ( 40 ) , RcsB ( 41 ) , RﬂM ( 42 ) , CsrA ( 43 ) , FimZ ( 44 ) , HilD ( 45 ) , cyclic AMP ( cAMP ) - cAMP receptor protein ( CRP ) complex ( cAMP-CRC ) and H-NS ( 46 ) , and YdiV ( 47 ) , as well as other mechanisms .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=26056383" target="_blank">26056383</a>]<br></li>
<li>H-NS is a nucleoid structuring protein and a global regulator of transcription in Salmonella and related Gram-negative bacteria such as E. coli and Yersinia ( 43 -- 45 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21059643" target="_blank">21059643</a>]<br></li>
<li>Regulation of csgD expression is known to be complex , involving multiple transcriptional regulatory proteins , small RNAs ( sRNAs ) , and histone-like proteins , such as H-NS and integration host factor ( IHF ) ( 42 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27260360" target="_blank">27260360</a>]<br></li>
<li>Transcription of hilA is subject to direct or indirect negative control by multiple nucleoid binding proteins , including Hha , H-NS , HU , and Fis ( 10 , 23 ) , and other proteins , including HilE , Pag , and Ams ( 5 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15126488" target="_blank">15126488</a>]<br></li>
<li>For example , DNA bending and supercoiling may regulate virulence genes as suggested by findings that the small nucleoid binding proteins IHF and H-NS reduce expression of spvR and spvABCD respectively ( O'Byrne and Dorman , 1994 ; Marshall et al. , 1999 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10844688" target="_blank">10844688</a>]<br></li>
<li>In E. coli , by SELEX screening , LeuO was found to regulate genes involved in sulfa drug sensitivity and to increase its own expression during transition into stationary phase and after a week of culture , where H-NS concentration decreased ( Figure 1 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=25566242" target="_blank">25566242</a>]<br></li>
<li>A number of transcriptional activators , including PhoP , SlyA , and LeuO , have been shown to antagonize H-NS silencing in E. coli and S. Typhimurium ( 86 -- 91 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=25916986" target="_blank">25916986</a>]<br></li>
<li>LeuO and H-NS are involved in regulation of leuO and ompS1 ( 2 , 5 ) , in addition to bgl , cadC , dsrA , and rovA ( 27 , 45 , 50 , 55 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18156266" target="_blank">18156266</a>]<br></li>
