<li>[ 10 ] Robbe-Saule V , Schaeffer F , Kowarz L , Norel F. Relationships between H-NS , sigma S , SpvR and growth phase in the control of spvR , the regulatory gene of the Salmonella plasmid virulence operon .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=14726232" target="_blank">14726232</a>]<br></li></div>
<li>The StpA-dependent genes of S. Typhimurium are a speciﬁc subset of the H-NS regulon that are predominantly under the positive control of s38 ( RpoS ) , CRP-cAMP and PhoP .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19843227" target="_blank">19843227</a>]<br></li>
<li>The assimilation of newly acquired genes into the regulons of H-NS , PhoP-PhoQ , and SsrA-SsrB , has allowed for the expansion of ﬂexible genetic networks that mediate bacterial pathogenesis and confer pathoadaptive ﬁtness differences .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=29034217" target="_blank">29034217</a>]<br></li>
<li>In E. coli , the presence of an hns mutation decreased the transcription of ﬂhD and ﬂiA genes required for the synthesis of ﬂagella ( 7 , 46 ) , a rather rare example of H-NS acting as a positive regulator .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=14761985" target="_blank">14761985</a>]<br></li>
<li>Also , in E. coli , the effect of H-NS on iron acquisition is divergent ; it acts as a repressor of salmochelin ( IroN ) and activator of the hemin receptor ( ChuA ) , while having no effect on the expression of enterobactin receptor ( FebA ) ( 43 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21075923" target="_blank">21075923</a>]<br></li>
<li>The transcription of sdiA and hns in these recombinant plasmids is under the control of the promoter of the Kanr gene of the pACYC177 vector which allows a constitutive expression of SdiA or H-NS .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=25080967" target="_blank">25080967</a>]<br></li>
