<li>A well-known gene encodes for nucleotide-associated protein ( H-NS ) , a histone-like nucleotide-structuring protein , which has been associated with virulence factors as a temperaturedependent phenotype ( 65 -- 70 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=28660201" target="_blank">28660201</a>]<br></li>
