<li>However , in other systems , such as the E. coli ler operon and the S. enterica hilA promoter , puriﬁed Hha seems to be able to bind DNA independently of H-NS ( 16 , 36 , 45 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17675384" target="_blank">17675384</a>]<br></li>
<li>H-NS is known to repress its own promoter , and the H-NSR12H mutation may impair the ability of H-NS to auto-regulate its expression ( 51 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23515315" target="_blank">23515315</a>]<br></li>
